:: Call to Adventure {"position":"900,525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="narrative">
Days later, that utopian image shatters. An urgent summons appears on your datapad: "Requesting your presence. Mayor Alden." You are escorted to City Hall, a stark contrast of old-world marble and hyper-modern security drones. Inside his sprawling office, Mayor Alden looks exhausted, his usually immaculate suit rumpled.
</div>

<img src="images/mayor_alden_stressed.gif" alt="A middle-aged man in a suit looking stressed, with a chaotic city view behind him.">

<div class="narrative">
"Sophia," he begins, his voice strained, "you're one of the brightest minds on AI ethics at the Institute. We have a crisis." On the wall-sized screen behind him, news feeds show glitching traffic drones, angry parents protesting biased school grading systems, and headlines screaming about AI-driven misinformation.
</div>

[[You feel a knot of doubt tighten in your stomach.->Refusal and Mentor]]


:: Challenge 1 - School Bias Intro {"position":"900,775","size":"100,100"}
<div class="narrative">
Holding the Codex, you feel a spark of determination. Your first lead takes you to the green campus of Technovia High. There, amidst anxious students, you find your first ally: Kai. He's a young, earnest student leader, clutching a tablet full of damning data.
</div>

<img src="images/kai_pleading.gif" alt="A young man with black hair in a red hoodie, looking worried and pleading.">

<div class="narrative">
In a quiet corner of the school library, Kai shows you the data. The graphs are undeniable: the AI grading system is consistently giving lower scores to students from specific districts. "It's not just unfair, it's ruining futures," he says, his voice tense. "We have to do something, Sophia. What's the plan?"
</div>

[[Advise Kai that the most effective solution is to retrain the AI with diverse and representative data.->School Bias - Choice A]]

[[Demand that the school remove the AI grading system entirely.->School Bias - Choice B]]

[[Tell Kai that the current system, while flawed, should be kept in place to avoid disruption.->School Bias - Choice C]]


:: Challenge 2 - TalentScan Intro {"position":"775,1150","size":"100,100"}
<div class="narrative">
Lena brings you to a small, crowded community hall. The air is thick with frustration and despair. She introduces you to a group of job applicants, all highly qualified, with impressive resumes, but all rejected by "TalentScan," Technovia's automated hiring system.
</div>

<img src="images/community_hall.gif" alt="A small, crowded room with diverse people talking, looking concerned.">

<div class="narrative">
They all have one thing in common: they live in the city's most diverse districts. The AI's decision process is a complete black box. Lena turns to you, her recorder already active. "What's your first move to bring this injustice to light?"
</div>

[[Demand a full, transparent audit of TalentScan's training data and algorithm to identify the source of the bias.->TalentScan - Choice A]]

[[Launch a public campaign denouncing TalentScan without offering a specific solution.->TalentScan - Choice B]]

[[Advise the applicants to change their resumes to try and "trick" the algorithm.->TalentScan - Choice C]]


:: Challenge 3 - Smart City Intro {"position":"650,1525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="narrative">
The Mayor gestures to the panoramic window. "Sophia, our 'Omni-Sense' network manages everything from traffic flow to energy grids by collecting citizen data. It’s efficient, but public trust is at an all-time low after a minor data breach. People are terrified of this surveillance. How do I fix this while keeping our city functional?"
</div>

[[Recommend that the Mayor launch a program that champions data minimization and anonymization.->Smart City - Choice A]]

[[Recommend that the Mayor increase data security and encryption but continue collecting all data.->Smart City - Choice B]]

[[Recommend that the Mayor publicly assure citizens that their data is safe without providing specific policy changes.->Smart City - Choice C]]


:: Challenge 4 - Autonomous Transport Intro {"position":"525,1900","size":"100,100"}
<div class="narrative">
The lead engineer, a woman named Dr. Anya Sharma, gestures to the holographic pods zipping around the map. "We are ready to build a city-wide Autonomous Public Transport system. But before we write a single line of code, we need an ethical framework. It must be our north star for the entire project. Sophia, what should that guiding philosophy be?"
</div>

<img src="images/dr_sharma.gif" alt="A confident woman with a lab coat, gesturing towards a holographic blueprint.">

[[Propose a comprehensive framework emphasizing transparency (XAI), accountability, and human oversight.->APT - Choice A]]

[[Propose a simple rule: minimize the overall number of injuries in any potential accident.->APT - Choice B]]

[[Propose that the system must prioritize passenger safety above all else.->APT - Choice C]]


